    {
      "id": "l1-greetings",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Greetings and politeness",
      "body": "# Greetings\n\nA few words cover most polite first contact in English:\n\n- **Hello** (नमस्ते) — works any time of day\n- **Good morning** (सुप्रभात) — until noon\n- **Thank you** (धन्यवाद) — to thank someone\n- **Please** (कृपया) — to make a request polite\n- **Goodbye** (अलविदा) — when leaving\n\nUnlike Hindi, English does not change the verb for respect (आप vs तुम). \"Hello\" and \"Thank you\" are the same for everyone — politeness comes from words like *please* and *thank you*, not from the verb form."
    },
    {
      "id": "l1-ex-match-greetings",
      "type": "exercise",
      "theory_ref": "l1-greetings",
      "title": "Match the greetings",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l1-ex-match-greetings",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each English word with its Hindi meaning.",
        "card_ids": [
          "hi-hello",
          "hi-thank-you",
          "hi-please",
          "hi-goodbye"
        ],
        "pairs": [
          {
            "left": "Hello",
            "right": "नमस्ते"
          },
          {
            "left": "Thank you",
            "right": "धन्यवाद"
          },
          {
            "left": "Please",
            "right": "कृपया"
          },
          {
            "left": "Goodbye",
            "right": "अलविदा"
          }
        ],
        "direction": "target_to_source"
      }
    },
