    },
    {
      "id": "l1-numbers",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Numbers 1 to 5",
      "body": "# Numbers 1-5\n\n- **One** (एक)\n- **Two** (दो)\n- **Three** (तीन)\n- **Four** (चार)\n- **Five** (पाँच)\n\nEnglish numbers do not change with gender or case, so *two* is always *two* — simpler than the noun system you may know from other languages."
    },
